org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.opmode

Class ClassManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.internal.opmode.ClassManager

  • public class ClassManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Finds all of the classes in the APK and provides an extensible mechanism for iterating and selecting classes for particular needs. Classes that want to select particular classes should implement ClassFilter and register themselves here. See ClassManagerFactory.

    This is predicated on the notion that the set of classes in any given APK is constant. So a class may implement ClassFilter, populate a static list of classes it is interested in, and then use that static list in any instance of the class knowing that the list is not dynamic over any given install of the APK. See AnnotatedOpModeRegistrar.
